\begin_layout Definition
A 
\emph on
random element
\emph default
 is a measurable function 
\begin_inset Formula $\X:\left(\Om_{1},\cA_{1}\right)\to\left(\Om_{2},\cA_{2}\right)$
\end_inset

 between measurable spaces.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\Om_{2}=\RR^{n}$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\NN$
\end_inset

, with 
\begin_inset Formula $\cA_{2}$
\end_inset

 the Borel 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-algebra on 
\begin_inset Formula $\RR^{n}$
\end_inset

, then we say 
\begin_inset Formula $\X$
\end_inset

 is a 
\emph on
random vector
\emph default
.
 A one-dimensional random vector is a 
\emph on
random variable
\emph default
.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\Om_{2}$
\end_inset

 is countable then we say 
\begin_inset Formula $\X$
\end_inset

 is 
\emph on
discrete
\emph default
.
\end_layout

