\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To interpret a random variable, we need a probability measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\Pr$
\end_inset

 on the underlying measurable space 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\Om_{1},\cA_{1}\right)$
\end_inset

 (often, this will be implicit).
 Then, 
