 the kernel of 
\begin_inset Formula $\To$
\end_inset

 is complementable.
 That is, there is a closed subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $S\subseteq\Fo$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $S\oplus\ker\To=\Fo$
\end_inset

.
 For example, this condition will always be satisfied if 
\begin_inset Formula $\Fo$
\end_inset

 is (isomorphic to a) Hilbert space, by the existence of orthogonal complements.
 In fact, Hilbert spaces are the only spaces where every closed subspace
 is complementable 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
