\begin_inset Formula $\To$
\end_inset

 restricts to a linear operator 
\begin_inset Formula $\T':S\to\im\To$
\end_inset

 between Banach spaces.
 By construction, 
\begin_inset Formula $\T'$
\end_inset

 is bijective so by the bounded inverse theorem, 
\begin_inset Formula $\T'$
\end_inset

 has a bounded inverse 
\begin_inset Formula $\U':\im\To\to S$
\end_inset

.
